# clawdputer / retro app — ROM source manifests
#
# Copy this file to your SD card as /roms/sources.txt to override the
# firmware's compiled-in defaults. Each non-comment line is a manifest URL.
#
# A manifest URL is either:
#   - An HTML page — the downloader scrapes <a href> values pointing at
#     supported ROM extensions (.gb, .gbc, plus future cores).
#   - A plain-text file — one ROM URL per line, optionally prefixed with
#     "Display name | " to override the displayed name. '#' starts a
#     line comment.
#
# Optional "Display | URL" syntax works in this file too — useful if a
# URL is opaque.

# --- ROM sites ---
Game Boy ROMs | https://www.romsgames.net/roms/gameboy/
Game Boy Color ROMs | https://www.romsgames.net/roms/gameboy-color/

# --- Homebrew (legit, public-domain games) ---
Homebrew Hub — Game Boy | https://gbhh.avivace.com/

# --- Your own manifest (example) ---
# Host a plain-text list of URLs on a gist / pastebin / your own server:
# My Game Boy library | https://gist.githubusercontent.com/USER/HASH/raw/manifest.txt
#
# Sample manifest contents (one URL per line):
#   https://example.com/roms/tetris.gb
#   Pokemon Red | https://example.com/roms/pokemon_red.gbc
#   # comments here ignored
